<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taylor and Tennessee -- together again. 
</P>
<P>
Elizabeth Taylor, who's given Oscar-nominated performances in film adaptations 
of the Tennessee Williams plays "Cat on a Hot Tin Roof" and "Suddenly, Last 
Summer," team up again on one of the writer's other well-known works. 
</P>
<P>
Taylor plays aging movie queen Alexandra del Lago opposite Mark Harmon as her 
manipulative lover Chance Wayne in a new version of Williams' "Sweet Bird of 
Youth." The two-hour NBC movie airs Sunday at 9 p.m. on Channels 4, 36 and 39. 
</P>
<P>
Also in the cast are Rip Torn as local town boss Tom Finley, Valerie Perrine as 
his alcoholic mistress and Cheryl Paris as Chance's childhood sweetheart. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, (Cover) Elizabeth Taylor and Mark Harmon Steve Fontanini / Los 
Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
