<TEXT>
<P>
I am writing regarding the KABC-TV story covering the Cleland House Community 
Center in East Los Angeles, which appeared on the station's 6 p.m. news on 
Sept. 12. Too many times the Mexican-American community receives attention from 
the media only when there are negative or sensational stories to report. I 
appreciate and applaud the decision to highlight the positive programs, 
activities, staff and clients at Cleland House. 
</P>
<P>
Mary R. Ortiz, Highland Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
