<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOME COOKIN'? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eating out home-style is not having to say thank you when you leave. 
</P>
<P>
Aunt Kizzy's Back Porch, 4325 Glencoe Ave., Marina del Rey. (213) 578-1005. 
Style: Huge portions of down-home Southern. Setting: Humble store-front with 
red bandanna prints. Recommended: Jambalaya; collard greens; fried chicken. 
Cost per person: $10-$15. 
</P>
<P>
Fama, 1416 4th St., Santa Monica. (213) 451-8633. Style: Upscale home-style 
Italian for yuppies. Setting: Woodworker goes awry. Recommended: Pork 
tenderloin cacciatore; pizza; apple crisp with vanilla ice cream. Cost per 
person: $15-$25. 
</P>
<P>
Grand House, 809 S. Grand Ave., San Pedro. (213) 548-1240. Style: Converted old 
house serving haute home cooking. Setting: Old-fashioned romance. Recommended: 
Menu changes daily, but might include rack of lamb; basil fettuccine with deer 
sausage; apple walnut cake. Cost per person: $20-$35. 
</P>
<P>
Paseo Real, 5342 Vineland Avenue, N. Hollywood, (818) 506-9166. Ctyle: 
Latin-American, prepared in a manana manner. Setting: Small, unself-consciously 
retro. Recommended: Pipian, pork in pumpkin seed sauce; fish in garlic sauce; 
brochette of shrimp with bacon and green pepper. Cost per person: $10-$15. 
</P>
<P>
Pho So 1, 7231 Reseda Blvd., Reseda. (818) 996-6515. Style: Vietnamese answer 
to Art's Deli. Setting: Rec room. Recommended: Pho dac biet, bits of brisket, 
tripe and beef in noodle soup; bun thit, noodle salad; bo bay mon, 7 course 
beef dinner. Cost per person: $3-$10. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
