</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding Lawrence Christon's article "Live from New York" (Sept. 17), I am 
shocked that he neglected to mention one of the most extraordinarily accurate 
satirists of the last 15 years: Christopher Guest. Not only was he arguably the 
main component of the National Lampoon Radio Hour, but for two seasons he 
astonished us with his comedic flexibility, musical prowess and character 
subtlety. 
</P>
<P>
TONY FORKUSH 
</P>
<P>
Hollywood 
</P>
