<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAST DAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The litany about the loss of KFAC as a classical music station has offered 
little in the way of a practical stratagem to restore this asset. I believe the 
following has merit: Listen to the new KFAC long enough to identify the 
sponsors. Write a letter to them (with a copy to KFAC) saying you will not buy 
their goods or service as long as they support KFAC as a rock broadcaster. It 
is possible that without donations, without foundation grants and with the 
voice of those who love classical music, the Philistines may yet be beaten at 
their own money game. 
</P>
<P>
LAWRENCE A. SHAPIRO 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 
</P>
