<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUST FOLLOWING THE LEADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It should come as no surprise, but probably will, to the artsy-smartsy View 
readers who have an abiding disdain for Lt. North, a retired U.S. Marine 
colonel, that such a man would devote "14 hours a day, five or six days a week 
. . . and is doing something for us somewhere, every day" according to John 
Staggers of the Alliance to Save America's Future (SAFE). 
</P>
<P>
This kind of work is tailor-made for North; after all, he has fought his 
country's battles before with dedication and honor. If we are to fight a "war 
on drugs," no one is better qualified to carry out that mission into the 
streets than is North. 
</P>
<P>
EDWIN O. LEARNARD, San Diego 
</P>
