CONFERENCE AND TRADE SHOW SET FOR COMMUNITY ASSOCIATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Community Associations Institute will present its annual educational 
conference and trade show on Oct. 14 at the Holiday Inn Crown Plaza, 5985 W. 
Century Blvd., Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The all-day event, starting with registration at 9:30 a.m. and ending at 5 
p.m., will offer three concurrent sessions covering management, accounting, 
legal and maintenance issues of interest to condominium owners and members of 
homeowners' associations. 
</P>
<P>
Morning sessions will feature Jerry Murase on the topic of disputes through 
arbitration; Steve L. Kanne will update the associations' governing documents 
and Lloyd Kennedy will focus on stretching the landscape dollar. Featured 
luncheon speakers include James Sweatt, Daniel Shapiro and David Regenbaum. 
</P>
<P>
Early afternoon topics will range from management ethics to investing 
association funds to asbestos issues with speakers David Regenbaum, Nico F. 
March, Larry Pothast, Gary E. Hamilton, Donald Boatwright and Michael Long. 
Other sessions will deal with roofing problems, researching construction 
defects and reserves. Peter Van Dijk, Gary Scholten, Roger M. Howard, Max 
Schartz, Robert N. Nordlund and Steven Besser are the featured experts. 
</P>
<P>
Registration fees are $65 for CAI members; $80 for non-members and $10 less for 
each additional registrant from the same association or firm; further 
information on the conference and trade fair may be obtained by calling (213) 
285-8286. 
</P>
</TEXT>
