<P>
</P>
<P>
Cool-season grasses including annual rye over Bermuda grass lawns, perennial 
rye, bluegrass, fescue. 
</P>
<P>
All California natives, including wildflowers, from seed. 
</P>
<P>
Most shrubs, trees, ground covers and vines. 
</P>
<P>
Note: This is not the best time of year to plant citrus, subtropical vines or 
shrubs, deciduous fruit trees such as apples or apricots, roses, or subtropical 
lawn grasses such as Bermuda or St. Augustine. All of these plants are about to 
go dormant or may freeze. 
</P>
