<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEEKING PREVENTION OF ALCOHOL ABUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On behalf of the Commission of Alcoholism, I want to commend you and John 
Mitchell for the excellent article on Sept. 3, 1989, "All-Out Against Alcohol." 
The article was a meaningful one. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Trisha Roth is a courageous citizen who has been willing to take on an 
unpopular position. We need more people like her in Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
The Times is to be congratulated for allowing its readers to know what some 
citizens are doing in the prevention of alcohol use by minors, drinking-driver 
accidents and the misuse of alcoholic beverages by adults. 
</P>
<P>
Keep up the good work, L.A. Times. 
</P>
<P>
BRUCE A. AULT, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
