<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO. 3 CORNHUSKERS DEFEAT OREGON STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LINCOLN, Neb. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oregon State lost to third-ranked Nebraska, 35-7, Saturday in a game that was 
closer than the score indicates. 
</P>
<P>
The Beavers trailed, 21-7, after Pat Chaffey scored on a two-yard run with 2:10 
left in the third quarter, and if it hadn't been for three Oregon State 
turnovers, it could have been close to the finish. 
</P>
<P>
Nebraska scored after all three turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
Nebraska, ranked second nationally in rushing with an average of 394 yards per 
game, managed only 193 yards through three quarters. Nebraska finished with 278 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterback Gerry Gdowski ran for one touchdown and passed for another to lead 
the Cornhuskers (4-0) over the Beavers (2-2). 
</P>
<P>
Nebraska Coach Tom Osborne sounded as if his team had lost. "Hang with us, 
don't give up on us," he said. "We're going to get better." 
</P>
<P>
Gdowski ran seven yards for Nebraska's first score as he capped the opening 
42-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
Bryan Carpenter added an eight-yard touchdown run early in the second quarter 
after a fumble recovery by Nebraska's Mike Petko at the Oregon State 35. 
</P>
<P>
Bruce Pickens intercepted a pass by Nick Schichtle to end an Oregon State drive 
in the third quarter. Nebraska's Richard Bell then went 48 yards to help set up 
a two-yard touchdown run by Ken Clark to give the Cornhuskers a 21-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Chaffey's touchdown came after Schichtle threw 39 yards to Maurice Wilson and 
had 16-yard completions to Jason Kent and Phil Ross. 
</P>
<P>
Gdowski then found Jon Bostick on a 60-yard touchdown pass play just over a 
minute after Husker safety Reggie Cooper intercepted another pass by Schichtle. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore quarterback Mike Grant added another Nebraska touchdown when he 
passed nine yards to Mark Dowse with 4:34 to play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
