<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCGWIRE'S 510 YARDS LEAD AZTECS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SALT LAKE CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dan McGwire threw for 510 yards and two touchdowns to lead San Diego State to a 
38-27 Western Athletic Conference victory over Utah Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
The game was tied, 21-21, after three quarters, but San Diego State (1-2 
overall and 1-1 in the conference) scored 17 points in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Andy Trakas' 26-yard field goal with 13:46 left put the Aztecs ahead for good, 
24-21. Ron Slack then scored on a two-yard run, and Darrin Wagner had a 19-yard 
touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
Wagner also had a 57-yard touchdown reception on a pass from McGwire and 
four-yard run, both in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
After Wagner's 57-yard catch gave San Diego State a 14-13 early in the third 
quarter, the Utes (1-4, 0-2) came back with Darrel Hicks' 33-yard touchdown 
reception from Scott Mitchell to put the Utes ahead, 19-14. Clifton Smith then 
caught a two-point conversion pass from Mitchell. 
</P>
<P>
Wagner's four-yard run tied the score, 21-21, with 7:12 left in the third 
quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
