<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROCKS UNDER BRIDGES DISPLACE THE HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a result of working as a volunteer at the Friendship Shelter for the 
homeless in Laguna Beach, I have become aware that miracles do happen. 
</P>
<P>
Because residents receive temporary housing, food, job training skills, 
counseling, money management, genuine caring, many residents graduate into the 
mainstream of society to jobs, and to their own apartment or room. One recent 
graduate had been on the streets for 11 years. 
</P>
<P>
They bank their job earnings to acquire first and last months' rent. The 
director, the Rev. Colin Henderson, does a masterful job of enforcing strict 
house rules, at the same time helping each resident with his needs. 
</P>
<P>
HAZEL LAFLER 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Niguel 
</P>
</TEXT>
