</P>
<P>
RABBITT LEADS IRVINE WOMEN TO THIRD AT UC RIVERSIDE CROSS-COUNTRY MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paced by junior Buffy Rabbitt, the UC Irvine women's cross-country team 
finished third at the UC Riverside Invitational Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Rabbitt finished second individually with a time of 17 minutes 18 seconds on 
the 5,000-meter course. Darcy Arreola of Cal State Northridge was first with a 
time of 17:13. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine had two other top 10 finishers in the 10-team race: Reyna Cervantes 
finished sixth and Roberta Moronez finished seventh with identical times of 
18:08. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine's B team in the men's division finished fifth. Dan Galdino was Irvine's 
top runner, finishing 25th with a time of 25:38 on the 8,000-meter course. 
</P>
<P>
At the New Mexico State golf classic in Las Cruces, N.M., Irvine is 16th after 
36 holes. 
</P>
<P>
Texas Christian's Mark Massengale is the individual leader with a four-under 
par 140 and Irvine's Mark Wilson and Lyle Archer are tied for 28th at 149. 
</P>
