<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUNIOR COLLEGE FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN LINDSEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
L.A. Southwest 12, Valley 9 -- A holding penalty on the final play of the game 
wiped out what would have been the winning touchdown for Valley in a Western 
State Conference opener at Los Angeles Southwest College. 
</P>
<P>
With no time left, Valley quarterback Mark Mengoli threw a 12-yard pass to 
tight end Sean Brown for a touchdown and an apparent victory, but the play was 
nullified by the penalty. 
</P>
<P>
Southwest improved to 3-0 overall and 2-0 in the WSC Northern Division. Valley 
fell to 0-3, 0-2 in the Southern Division. 
</P>
<P>
Southwest scored the decisive points in the fourth quarter on a pair of Jason 
Thomson field goals. The first, from 26 yards with 11:34 left, tied the score, 
9-9. The second, from 17 yards, came with 2:40 left. 
</P>
<P>
Craig Manigo completed eight of 16 passes for 80 yards and scored the only 
Southwest touchdown on an 18-yard run in the first quarter. On the extra-point 
attempt, Valley blocked the kick and Scott Holden recovered and ran the ball 
back 97 yards for a safety. KEVIN LINDSEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
