<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The six-month jail term of Christina LoCasto, a New York woman who gave birth 
in a jetliner restroom then abandoned her newborn infant in a wastebasket, has 
been delayed because she is expecting again. LoCasto, 27, of Staten Island, was 
scheduled to begin serving time in Redwood City on Oct. 14 after she pleaded no 
contest earlier this year to child endangerment. She was on a flight from 
Newark, N.J., to San Francisco in 1988 when she went into labor and delivered a 
baby girl, Alyssa, in a DC-10 restroom. She wrapped the infant in paper towels 
and abandoned her in a waste basket beneath the sink, where it was later 
discovered by a cleaning crew. LoCasto, who has two older daughters, ages 8 and 
2, is expecting her fourth child at the end of October, after which she will 
begin serving her sentence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
