<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 KILLED, 1 HURT WHEN PLANE CRASHES IN PASTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GREENCASTLE, Ind. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A single-engine plane clipped some trees, plunged into a cow pasture and burst 
into flames, killing three people, but a woman walked away from the wreckage 
Friday night with only minor injuries, authorities said. She was listed in 
satisfactory condition, a hospital spokesman said Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
