<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: FANS DONATE $53,000 FOR HURRICANE VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Carolina came away from Athens, Ga., with more than a 24-20 upset of 
23rd-ranked Georgia Saturday when the East Georgia chapter of the American Red 
Cross collected in excess of $53,000 to help in the relief effort from 
Hurricane Hugo. 
</P>
<P>
University of Georgia spokesman Tom Jackson said cash and check donations 
totaled $53,000 from the crowd of 84,000, and coins collected will be 
machine-counted today. 
</P>
<P>
"In my experience, I've never seen this much cash come in at one time in any 
day to any charity," said Frank Pfennig, executive director of the East Georgia 
chapter of the American Red Cross, headquartered in Athens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
AMERICAN RED CROSS; FUND RAISING; HURRICANES; DISASTER RELIEF; STORMS -- SOUTH 
CAROLINA; FOOTBALL GAMES; COLLEGE ATHLETICS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
