<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carlos Fuentes, the Mexican novelist, critic and diplomat, visits Cal State 
Fullerton Tuesday as part of a lecture tour of universities. He is the author 
of "The Death of Artemio Cruz" and the just-published "Christopher Unborn." He 
served as Mexico's ambassador to France from 1975 to 1977. 
</P>
<P>
Fuentes will discuss his works in a free public lecture at Cal State Fullerton. 
He will return to Orange County on Oct. 10 for a lecture sponsored by UC Irvine 
at South Coast Community Church. A film version of one of Fuentes' recent 
novels, "Old Gringo," opens in the United States this week and stars Jane 
Fonda, Gregory Peck and Jimmy Smits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
