BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Fullerton Fire Department will ask the City Council Tuesday to ban the sale 
and use of the so-called "safe and sane" fireworks, although most council 
members say they would like to keep them legal. The fire chief asked the 
council to consider the ban after he collected information showing that Orange 
County cities that have banned fireworks have far fewer fireworks-related fires 
than cities where the fireworks are allowed. 
</P>
