<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIT-RUN ACCIDENT KILLS ANAHEIM MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police were searching Saturday for the driver of a black Chevrolet Camaro who 
struck and killed a 20-year-old Anaheim bicyclist in a hit-and-run accident in 
Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, Luis Daniel Govez Navarette, was riding a bicycle in the 100 block 
of East La Palma Avenue about 1:30 a.m. Saturday when he was struck, Police Lt. 
John Haradon said. Witnesses described the driver as an adult male. 
</P>
<P>
Navarette was in critical condition when paramedics arrived. He died at 4:10 
a.m. at UCI Medical Center in Orange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
