<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM WOMAN DIES AFTER CAR HITS HER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old Anaheim woman died Saturday of head injuries after she stepped 
from her parked pick-up truck and was struck by a car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, Amy S. Meston, was thrown about 50 feet in the accident, which 
occurred about 12:30 p.m. Saturday in the 1300 block of Romneya Drive in 
Anaheim, according to Lt. Ray Welch. She was taken to UCI Medical Center in 
Orange, where she died a short time later. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Meston was in the road when she was struck by a car driven by a 
26-year-old Anaheim man who was not charged. 
</P>
<P>
The accident is still under investigation, Welch said. 
</P>
